extends ../../../module_layout

block content

  .ui.container#raised-container
    .limit
      h1.ui.header.large#learn-title
        .content
          | Definitions
        button.ui.icon.button.m.left.right#volume-up-button
          i.volume.up.icon

      p <u>Identity Theft</u> is when your personal information is stolen and used against you.
      p <u>Personal Information</u> Information that can be used to distinguish or trace an individual’s identity, either alone or when combined with other information that is linked or linkable to a specific individual.
      p Here are some specific examples of personal information:
      .ui.bulleted.list 
        .item 
          strong Descriptors: 
          | full name, maiden name, alias, gender, race, date of birth
        .item 
          strong Identification numbers: 
          | social security number (SSN), passport number, driver’s license number, taxpayer identification number, patient identification number, financial account number, medicare number, or credit card number
        .item 
          strong Address information:
          | street address or email address
        .item 
          strong Account information 
          | bank account, social media account, shopping platform account, and the corresponding passwords
        .item 
          strong Phone numbers: 
          | full name, maiden name, alias, gender, race, date of birth

      
